HackBLR 2026 Submission — Problem Statement 3: Voice AI Agent for Accessibility & Societal Impact
A voice-first AI legal assistant that makes Indian law accessible to everyone — regardless of language, literacy or income.

The Problem
70% of Indians cannot access legal help. 
Lawyers are expensive, courts are intimidating and legal language is impenetrable. Most people don't even know their basic rights.

The Solution
LegalAI is a multilingual voice + text legal assistant powered by:
- 5 specialist AI agents running in parallel (Researcher, Practical Advisor, Law Advisor, Rights Specialist, Law & Order Specialist)
- Synthesizer agent combining their analyses into one optimal answer
- 8,000+ vector knowledge base sourced from credible open datasets
- Voice interface in 5 Indian languages: Hindi, Kannada, Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam

Architecture
User (Voice/Text)
↓
Vapi (Voice Layer) → STT (Deepgram) → LLM → TTS (ElevenLabs)
↓
FastAPI Backend
↓
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  LAYER 1: 5 Specialist Agents (parallel) │
│  - Researcher (statutes & sections)      │
│  - Practical Advisor (steps, costs)      │
│  - Law Advisor (case strength)           │
│  - Rights Specialist (legal rights)      │
│  - Law & Order Specialist (FIR, bail)    │
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘
↓
┌──────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  LAYER 2: Synthesizer Agent              │
│  Combines all 5 outputs into one answer  │
└──────────────────────────────────────────┘
↓
RAG Context from Qdrant (8,000+ vectors)
↓
Response (with cited sources)



Tech Stack
- Voice: Vapi (Deepgram STT + ElevenLabs TTS)
- LLM: Groq (llama-3.3-70b-versatile) with multi-model fallback
- Vector DB: Qdrant Cloud
- Embeddings: sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (local, no API limits)
- Backend: FastAPI + Python
- Frontend: Single-file HTML with Tailwind-style CSS

Knowledge Base Sources (All Credible, Open License)
1. IndicLegalQA — 10,000 QA pairs from Supreme Court judgments (Mendeley, CC BY 4.0)
2. Indian Legal QA — Akshat Gupta dataset (Kaggle, CC BY-SA 4.0)
3. Lawyer GPT India — nisaar (HuggingFace)
4. Constitution of India Instructions — nisaar (HuggingFace)
5. Indian Bare Acts — IPC, BNS, CrPC, BNSS, Contract Act, Constitution
6. Multiple HuggingFace datasets for legal text coverage

Total: 8,000+ vectors covering criminal law, civil law, constitutional law, family law, employment law, consumer rights, cyber crime and more.

Key Features
- Multi-Agent Legal Reasoning — 5 AI lawyers analyze every query in parallel
- New Criminal Law Coverage — Cites both old (IPC/CrPC/Evidence Act) AND new (BNS/BNSS/BSA) sections that took effect on 1 July 2024
- Multilingual — Hindi, Kannada, Telugu, Tamil, Malayalam + English
- Voice + Text — Same backend powers both
- Document Generation — Drafts legal notices as downloadable .docx files
- Contract Analysis — Clause-by-clause risk scoring
- Free Legal Aid Integration — Connects users to NALSA helpline (15100) and state legal services authorities

Roadmap (Round 2 Features)
- Emergency detection (domestic violence, cyber fraud, threats)
- Legal case strength scoring (1-10 scale)
- Evidence checklist generator
- Legal cost estimator
- State-wise legal aid finder
- Dual-LLM resilience (Groq + Gemini failover)

Project Structure
